# MCF Integration Guide for M3P Framework

## Overview

This document explains how to integrate the Multicommodity Flow (MCF) problem solver into your M3P framework to check if network N_k is "well-defined" at each stage k ≥ 5.

## Architecture

```
Lean4 (M3P Algorithm)
    ↓
    | Build MCFInput with commodities, capacities, constraints
    ↓
MCFInterface.lean
    ↓
    | Write JSON to /tmp/mcf_input.json
    ↓
networkx_mcf.py (Python)
    ↓
    | Solve LP using PuLP
    ↓
    | Write JSON to /tmp/mcf_output.json
    ↓
MCFInterface.lean
    ↓
    | Parse MCFResult
    ↓
M3P Algorithm (check wellDefined flag)
```

## Files Created

1. **networkx_mcf.py** - Python LP solver for MCF problem
2. **MCFInterface.lean** - Lean4 interface to Python solver
3. **test_mcf_solver.py** - Test suite for MCF solver

